cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.MM, cs.CR 

The paper deals with computer vision and machine learning techniques for face recognition, which are typically covered in the computer vision (cs.CV) and machine learning (cs.LG) sub-categories. The proposed method involves training a convolutional neural network, which falls under the artificial intelligence (cs.AI) sub-category. The use of the AR face database suggests a focus on multimedia (cs.MM) applications. Finally, the proposed loss function and its potential impact on security and privacy suggest a connection to the cryptography and security (cs.CR) sub-category.
